The paper deals with the complexity of approximating the partition function of the eight-vertex model on graphs, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves counting perfect matchings, which is a problem in combinatorial optimization and graph theory, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The paper also uses geometric lemmas, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
